  <section>
    <h2>1. The Three C’s</h2>
    <p><b>CHECK</b> – Ensure the area is safe.<br>
       <b>CALL</b> – Contact emergency services if needed.<br>
       <b>CARE</b> – Provide help until professionals arrive.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Common Injuries</h2>
    <h3>• Cuts & Scrapes</h3>
    <p>Wash hands, clean wound, apply antiseptic, cover with bandage.</p>
    <h3>• Nosebleeds</h3>
    <p>Lean forward, pinch nostrils for 10 minutes, avoid tilting head back.</p>
    <h3>• Burns</h3>
    <p>Cool under running water for 20 minutes, cover with clean cloth.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Serious Situations</h2>
    <h3>• Fainting</h3>
    <p>Lay person flat, elevate legs, ensure fresh air.</p>
    <h3>• Allergic Reactions</h3>
    <p>Call emergency services immediately, use epinephrine if prescribed.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. First Aid Kit Essentials</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Bandages and gauze pads</li>
      <li>Antiseptic wipes and ointments</li>
      <li>Cold pack</li>
      <li>Scissors and tweezers</li>
      <li>Emergency contact list</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

